## INCAR template for CPU VASP runs
## No GPU-specific settings needed; parallelism controlled by NPAR/KPAR

SYSTEM = your_system_name


Start parameter for this Run:
  NWRITE =  2;  LPETIM=F
  ISTART =  0                 job   : 0-new  1-cont  2-samecut
  LWAVE  =  .FALSE.
  LCHARG =  .FALSE.


Cluster dependent:
  KPAR   =  1                set to number of k-point groups (divides NKPTS)


Electronic Relaxation:
  ENCUT  =  800.00 EV        adjust for your system
  NELM   =  150
  EDIFF  =  1E-06
  ALGO   =  N
  LREAL  =  A


Ionic Relaxation:
  NSW    =  0                0 for single-point, >0 for MD/relaxation
  ISYM   =  0
  ISIF   =  2

  POTIM  =  1.000
  TEBEG  =  8000             initial temperature (for MD)
  SMASS  =  0.00


DOS related values:
  ISMEAR =  -1
  SIGMA  = 0.689387


## Notes:
## - Do NOT set NPAR for CPU runs -- let VASP auto-determine it (default is fine).
## - KPAR can be set to improve k-point parallelism if NKPTS > 1.
## - On DELTA, 128 cores (16 MPI x 8 OMP) and 96 cores give similar performance
##   for this benchmark system. Scaling is poor beyond 128 cores per node.
